                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="25" data-divcontentid="divContent_25" id="show_25" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-show-btn" style="display: block;"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i>
                                                        </a>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="25" data-divcontentid="divContent_25" id="hide_25" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-hide-btn hb-com" style="display: none;"><i class="fa fa-angle-up"></i>
                                                        </a>


                                                        <div id="divContent_25" class="time-hide m-t-20" style="display: none;">
                                                            <div class="col-md-12"><p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Yes, NUML provides transport facilities on specified routes within Islamabad, Rawalpindi, and Taxila/Wah. Students can avail themselves of the service at the beginning of each semester by applying through the transport section</span></span></span></span></p></div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </li>
                                                                                        <li class="bg_color_white">
                                                <div class="s17-eve-time">
                                                    <div class="s17-eve-time-msg w100 m-l-10">
                                                        <h4>Q.26	How can I transfer credit hours to NUML?</h4>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="26" data-divcontentid="divContent_26" id="show_26" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-show-btn" style="display: block;"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i>
                                                        </a>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="26" data-divcontentid="divContent_26" id="hide_26" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-hide-btn hb-com" style="display: none;"><i class="fa fa-angle-up"></i>
                                                        </a>


                                                        <div id="divContent_26" class="time-hide m-t-20" style="display: none;">
                                                            <div class="col-md-12"><p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">To transfer credit hours to NUML, you must submit a credit transfer application form (available on the NUML website) to the Academic Branch. The NUML committee will evaluate your transcript and issue a letter of acceptance or rejection based on its assessment. Please note that migration from local (twin cities) ,private universities/institutes, or sub-campuses is not allowed.</span></span></span></span></p></div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </li>
                                                                                        <li class="bg_color_white">
                                                <div class="s17-eve-time">
                                                    <div class="s17-eve-time-msg w100 m-l-10">
                                                        <h4>Q.27	I want to migrate from NUML to another university. What should I do?</h4>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="27" data-divcontentid="divContent_27" id="show_27" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-show-btn" style="display: block;"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i>
                                                        </a>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="27" data-divcontentid="divContent_27" id="hide_27" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-hide-btn hb-com" style="display: none;"><i class="fa fa-angle-up"></i>
                                                        </a>


                                                        <div id="divContent_27" class="time-hide m-t-20" style="display: none;">
                                                            <div class="col-md-12"><p><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Yes, you can. Please check the requirements with the host university</span></span><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">. </span></span></p></div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </li>
                                                                                        <li class="bg_color_white">
                                                <div class="s17-eve-time">
                                                    <div class="s17-eve-time-msg w100 m-l-10">
                                                        <h4>Q.28	How can I transfer from a NUML regional campus to the main campus?</h4>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="28" data-divcontentid="divContent_28" id="show_28" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-show-btn" style="display: block;"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i>
                                                        </a>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="28" data-divcontentid="divContent_28" id="hide_28" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-hide-btn hb-com" style="display: none;"><i class="fa fa-angle-up"></i>
                                                        </a>


                                                        <div id="divContent_28" class="time-hide m-t-20" style="display: none;">
                                                            <div class="col-md-12"><p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">To transfer from a NUML regional campus to the main campus, you must submit an application through the respective Regional Director for further processing, subject to the following conditions</span></span><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">: -</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">a.&nbsp;<span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Transfer from NUML Rawalpindi Campus is not allowed.</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">b. T<span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">ransfers during the 1<sup>st</sup> semester are not allowed</span>.</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">c. Transferred students will be placed in the <strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">afternoon shift</span></strong>. </span></span></span></span></p></div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </li>
                                                                                        <li class="bg_color_white">
                                                <div class="s17-eve-time">
                                                    <div class="s17-eve-time-msg w100 m-l-10">
                                                        <h4>Q.29	Can I change my campus after admission at Main Campus?</h4>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="29" data-divcontentid="divContent_29" id="show_29" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-show-btn" style="display: block;"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i>
                                                        </a>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="29" data-divcontentid="divContent_29" id="hide_29" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-hide-btn hb-com" style="display: none;"><i class="fa fa-angle-up"></i>
                                                        </a>


                                                        <div id="divContent_29" class="time-hide m-t-20" style="display: none;">
                                                            <div class="col-md-12"><p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Yes, a student can request a transfer to another campus, subject to the prescribed transfer policy</span></span><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">.</span></span></span></span></p></div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </li>
                                                                                        <li class="bg_color_white">
                                                <div class="s17-eve-time">
                                                    <div class="s17-eve-time-msg w100 m-l-10">
                                                        <h4>Q.30	How can I Freeze my semester?</h4>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="30" data-divcontentid="divContent_30" id="show_30" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-show-btn" style="display: block;"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i>
                                                        </a>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="30" data-divcontentid="divContent_30" id="hide_30" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-hide-btn hb-com" style="display: none;"><i class="fa fa-angle-up"></i>
                                                        </a>


                                                        <div id="divContent_30" class="time-hide m-t-20" style="display: none;">
                                                            <div class="col-md-12"><p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Semester freeze is permitted for up to two regular semesters (one semester only for higher studies) during coursework due to valid reasons, subject to approval by the competent authority. Applicable fees are 25%, 50%, or 100%, depending on whether the request is made within 30 days before midterms, or after midterms. However, freezing of the 1st semester is not allowed</span></span><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">.</span></span></span></span></p></div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </li>
                                                                                        <li class="bg_color_white">
                                                <div class="s17-eve-time">
                                                    <div class="s17-eve-time-msg w100 m-l-10">
                                                        <h4>Q.31	Are ceased students allowed for re-admission in the existing degree?</h4>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="31" data-divcontentid="divContent_31" id="show_31" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-show-btn" style="display: block;"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i>
                                                        </a>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="31" data-divcontentid="divContent_31" id="hide_31" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-hide-btn hb-com" style="display: none;"><i class="fa fa-angle-up"></i>
                                                        </a>


                                                        <div id="divContent_31" class="time-hide m-t-20" style="display: none;">
                                                            <div class="col-md-12"><p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Yes, students who have been declared as &quot;ceased&quot; are allowed to apply for re-admission into their existing degree program. Re-admission is permitted starting from the 5th semester onward and must be applied for in the regular semester immediately following the cessation.</span></span></span></span></p></div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </li>
                                                                                        <li class="bg_color_white">
                                                <div class="s17-eve-time">
                                                    <div class="s17-eve-time-msg w100 m-l-10">
                                                        <h4>Q.32	What is the status of the NUML, is it public or private?</h4>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="32" data-divcontentid="divContent_32" id="show_32" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-show-btn" style="display: block;"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i>
                                                        </a>
                                                        <a href="javascript:void(0);" data-id="32" data-divcontentid="divContent_32" id="hide_32" class="s17-sprit age-dwarr-btn time-hide-btn hb-com" style="display: none;"><i class="fa fa-angle-up"></i>
                                                        </a>


                                                        <div id="divContent_32" class="time-hide m-t-20" style="display: none;">
                                                            <div class="col-md-12"><p><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="background-color:white"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">NUML is a federally chartered public-sector university recognized by the HEC.</span></span></span></span></p></div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </li>
                                                                                    </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                                            </div>
